  "text": "The federally approved hESC-09-0013 cell line, deposited by the Rockefeller University (RUES2) was used in these studies. The RUES2 cell line was previously modified to include a genetically encoded calcium indicator, GCaMP, as described previously. [CITATION_1] This genetic modification allows live visualization of calcium transients in hESC-derived cardiac cells and in vivo grafts created from these cells. [CITATION_2] Expression of B2M in hESCs was permanently silenced by transduction with a lentiviral shRNA against human B2M. For simplicity, these cells are referred to as ''G-Par'' and ''G-Mod'' indicating parental RUES2-GCaMP and modified RUES2-GCaMP with downregulated B2M gene expression, respectively. B2M mRNA expression was decreased by 90% in G-Mod cells, compared with G-Par cells. Importantly, the expression levels of pluripotency genes were unchanged in G-Mod, as detected by qRT-PCR (Fig. 1A) .",
